Wash and dry all produce. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim @green beans{6%ounce}, if necessary; cut crosswise into 2-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}. Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, add green beans and a splash of water to a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}; cover with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}. Drain. Heat a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add @peanuts{1/2%ounce}, @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4), and @water{2%TBSP}. Cook, stirring, until water has evaporated and peanuts are coated and lightly toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}.

Wash out pan used for peanuts. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{4-6%minutes} (it'll cook through in the next step).

Stir green beans, scallion whites, remaining ginger, and @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4) into pan with pork. Cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until ginger is fragrant and pork is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: If scallions brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium low.

Stir in @szechuan paste{2%tablespoon}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, and @water{1/4%cup} (⅓ cup for 4). Cook, stirring, until everything is thoroughly coated, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with salt and @pepper{}. Divide between #bowls{}. Taste and season stir-fry with salt and pepper; spoon over rice. Sprinkle with scallion greens and peanuts. Serve.